</head>
<body>
    <header class="p-3 text-bg-dark">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="d-flex flex-wrap align-items-center justify-content-center justify-content-lg-start">
            <a href="/" class="d-flex align-items-center mb-2 mb-lg-0 text-white text-decoration-none">
              <svg class="bi me-2" width="40" height="32" role="img" aria-label="Bootstrap"><use xlink:href="#bootstrap"></use></svg>
            </a>
    
            <ul class="nav col-12 col-lg-auto me-lg-auto mb-2 justify-content-center mb-md-0">
                <li><a href="/" class="nav-link px-2 text-secondary">WeatherHub</a></li>
                <li><a href="/features" class="nav-link px-2 text-white">Features</a></li>
                <li><a href="/presearchlocation" class="nav-link px-2 text-white">Search Location</a></li>
                <li><a href="/about" class="nav-link px-2 text-white">About</a></li>
              </ul>
    
            <div class="text-end">
              <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-light me-2"><a class="line" href="/">Login</a></button>
              <button type="button" class="btn btn-warning"><a class="line" href="/registration">Register</a></button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </header>
  <header>
    <h1>Weather App Features</h1>
  </header>
  <main>
    <section>
      <h2>User Authentication</h2>
      <p>The weather application provides a secure user authentication system. Users can register, log in, and log out to personalize their experience and access additional features.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Recent Searches and Saved Locations</h2>
      <p>Once logged in, users have the convenience of viewing their recent weather searches and saved locations. This allows for quick access to frequently checked locations without the need to re-enter coordinates.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Interactive World Map</h2>
      <p>Explore the world map interactively by pointing the cursor to any location. The application will automatically retrieve the longitude and latitude coordinates, enabling users to check the current weather conditions and forecasts for that specific location.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>MySQL Database Integration</h2>
      <p>The backend of the application seamlessly integrates with a MySQL database. This ensures efficient storage and retrieval of user data, recent searches, and saved locations, enhancing the overall user experience.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Weather Data Retrieval</h2>
      <p>The application connects to a weather API to fetch real-time weather data and forecasts. Users can stay informed about the current weather conditions, temperature, humidity, and other relevant information for any location on the map.</p>
    </section>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
